Articles.Content:
Beyond Jool is a planet mod I've been wanting to make since I bought the game. The idea is it would not add new stars, but add new planets, mainly a new Saturn analog. I'm fine with no Uranus or Neptune analogs. This thread is mainly for help. This year I finally did something with it.

The "version history" is here.

Spoiler

0.1 Added Sarkin.

0.2 Added Lull.

0.2.1 Fixed Sarkin lighting.

0.2.2 Fixed Lull fading.

0.3 Added Sushut.

0.4 Added Rage.

0.5. Added Pebble.

0.5.1 Gave Sushut atmosphere.

0.5.2 Removed Pebble (for now) and retextured Sushut.

0.6 Gave Sushut AtmosphereFromGround node and added Sapp and Kotta. 

Sarkin is here

Spoiler

"Sarkin is the sixth planet in the Kerbol System, with it's large rings, and astounding size, it weird it hadn't been discovered... until now."

Lull is here.

Spoiler

"Lull is just a boring moon that looks a lot like the Mun. It, like the moons of Jool, was found after somekerb found a "grey dot" that wouldn't come off. However, its high inclination gives a nice view of Sarkin's rings."

Sushut is here.

Spoiler

"Sushut is massive. It has a small atmosphere, and is larger than Kerbin. It even has its own moon! It may be the hardest body to land on... It is named after the great planetary scientist Sushut Kerman, who figured out that Tylo was no mere smudge. (And then gave the tip to the KSC staff for that photo)"

Kotta is here.

Spoiler

"Kotta is the third major moon of Sarkin. Its only major feature are its many valleys and canyons. Otherwise, it's just another moon."

Sapp is here.

Spoiler

" A cold, icy moon, Sapp's name is an accident, as it was supposed to be Sapphire, but by the time it was known, Sapp's name was already in many places. It has rings and even orbits retrograde! However, it is very hilly, with not a lot of flat land."

And Rage, a planet closer to the Sun then Moho.

Spoiler

"Rage. A planet so close to Kerbol you may go blind trying to find it. Some say it is more like Moho in the stories then Moho."

What I need help with: 

1. Oceans, for Rage. (lava)

added stuff

Okay, I need help.. with this. The moon Kotta is not being oblate, even though I followed a tutorial using (and yes I have the right mod) @Lt_Duckweeds VertexHeightOblateAdvanced mod. I put it in the Mods subnode of the PQS node.

Pics here.

Spoiler

When I zoom out too much, this happens.

Things explode on teleportation.

And the map view doesn't  notice.
